import{c as t,Q as a,j as i,m as s}from"./chunks/framework.BXc4yaFE.js";const u=JSON.parse('{"title":"Fireside chat at Sequoia Ascent 2026 — LLM new horizons, jaggedness, agent-native economy — @karpathy","description":"","frontmatter":{"title":"Fireside chat at Sequoia Ascent 2026 — LLM new horizons, jaggedness, agent-native economy — @karpathy","author":"Andrej Karpathy（@karpathy）","date":"2026-04-30T00:00:00.000Z","source":"https://x.com/karpathy/status/2049903821095354523","type":"tweet"},"headers":[],"relativePath":"research/tweets/2026-04-30-@karpathy-354523.md","filePath":"research/tweets/2026-04-30-@karpathy-354523.md","lastUpdated":1779894392000}'),o={name:"research/tweets/2026-04-30-@karpathy-354523.md"};function n(r,e,l,d,c,h){return a(),i("div",null,[...e[0]||(e[0]=[s('<h1 id="fireside-chat-at-sequoia-ascent-2026-—-llm-new-horizons-jaggedness-agent-native-economy-—-karpathy" tabindex="-1">Fireside chat at Sequoia Ascent 2026 — LLM new horizons, jaggedness, agent-native economy — @karpathy <a class="header-anchor" href="#fireside-chat-at-sequoia-ascent-2026-—-llm-new-horizons-jaggedness-agent-native-economy-—-karpathy" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Fireside chat at Sequoia Ascent 2026 — LLM new horizons, jaggedness, agent-native economy — @karpathy&quot;">​</a></h1><p><strong>來源</strong>：<a href="https://x.com/karpathy/status/2049903821095354523" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">https://x.com/karpathy/status/2049903821095354523</a><strong>作者</strong>：Andrej Karpathy（@karpathy） <strong>發布日期</strong>：2026-04-30 <strong>收錄日期</strong>：2026-05-01 <strong>類型</strong>：推文 <strong>統計</strong>：4181 likes · 536 retweets · 4460 bookmarks · 495275 views</p><hr><h2 id="全文" tabindex="-1">全文 <a class="header-anchor" href="#全文" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;全文&quot;">​</a></h2><p>Fireside chat at Sequoia Ascent 2026 from a ~week ago. Some highlights:</p><p>The first theme I tried to push on is that LLMs are about a lot more than just speeding up what existed before (e.g. coding). Three examples of new horizons:</p><ol><li>menugen: an app that can be fully engulfed by LLMs, with no classical code needed: input an image, output an image and an LLM can natively do the thing.</li><li>install .md skills instead of install .sh scripts. Why create a complex Software 1.0 bash script for e.g. installing a piece of software if you can write the installation out in words and say &quot;just show this to your LLM&quot;. The LLM is an advanced interpreter of English and can intelligently target installation to your setup, debug everything inline, etc.</li><li>LLM knowledge bases as an example of something that was <em>impossible</em> with classical code because it&#39;s computation over unstructured data (knowledge) from arbitrary sources and in arbitrary formats, including simply text articles etc.</li></ol><p>I pushed on these because in every new paradigm change, the obvious things are always in the realm of speeding up or somehow improving what existed, but here we have examples of functionality that either suddenly perhaps shouldn&#39;t even exist (1,2), or was fundamentally not possible before (3).</p><p>The second (ongoing) theme is trying to explain the pattern of jaggedness in LLMs. How it can be true that a single artifact will simultaneously 1) coherently refactor a 100,000-line code base <em>and</em> 2) tell you to walk to the car wash to wash your car. I previously wrote about the source of this as having to do with verifiability of a domain, here I expand on this as having to also do with economics because revenue/TAM dictates what the frontier labs choose to package into training data distributions during RL. You&#39;re either in the data distribution (on the rails of the RL circuits) and flying or you&#39;re off-roading in the jungle with a machete, in relative terms. Still not 100% satisfied with this, but it&#39;s an ongoing struggle to build an accurate model of LLM capabilities if you wish to practically take advantage of their power while avoiding their pitfalls, which brings me to...</p><p>Last theme is the agent-native economy. The decomposition of products and services into sensors, actuators and logic (split up across all of 1.0/2.0/3.0 computing paradigms), how we can make information maximally legible to LLMs, some words on the quickly emerging agentic engineering and its skill set, related hiring practices, etc., possibly even hints/dreams of fully neural computing handling the vast majority of computation with some help from (classical) CPU coprocessors.</p><hr><h2 id="研究摘要" tabindex="-1">研究摘要 <a class="header-anchor" href="#研究摘要" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;研究摘要&quot;">​</a></h2><p><strong>TL;DR</strong>：LLM 的核心價值不是加速現有工作，而是創造以前不可能存在的產品；jaggedness 源自 economics（RL 訓練資料分佈由 revenue/TAM 決定）；未來是 agent-native economy。</p><h3 id="核心論點" tabindex="-1">核心論點 <a class="header-anchor" href="#核心論點" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;核心論點&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>LLM 最大價值在「新可能性」而非「加速舊工作」：menugen（純 LLM app，無傳統程式碼）、.md skills 取代 .sh scripts、LLM knowledge base（以前用程式碼根本不可能）</li><li>Jaggedness 的新解釋：不只是 verifiability，更是 economics — RL 訓練資料由 revenue/TAM 驅動，在高價值領域模型能力被「焊死在軌道上」，其他領域靠泛化硬闖</li><li>Agent-native economy：產品與服務分解為 sensors/actuators/logic，橫跨 Software 1.0/2.0/3.0 三種範式</li><li>未來可能：neural nets 承擔大部分運算，CPU 退化為確定性工具呼叫的 coprocessor</li><li>Agentic engineering 是新興技能集，與 vibe coding 有本質差異</li></ul><h3 id="關鍵數據-工具" tabindex="-1">關鍵數據 / 工具 <a class="header-anchor" href="#關鍵數據-工具" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;關鍵數據 / 工具&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>menugen：純 LLM app，input image → output image，zero classical code</li><li>.md skills：用自然語言描述安裝意圖，LLM 自適應環境、debug inline</li><li>LLM knowledge base：computation over unstructured data，classical code 不可能實作</li><li>比喻：100K 行 codebase refactor vs. 走去洗車（同一模型的 jaggedness 極端案例）</li></ul><h3 id="批判性觀察" tabindex="-1">批判性觀察 <a class="header-anchor" href="#批判性觀察" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;批判性觀察&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>Karpathy 自承對 jaggedness 解釋「still not 100% satisfied」，economics 驅動論是假說而非確論，缺乏量化驗證</li><li>.md skills 取代 .sh scripts 在 cc-workspace 已是現實（CLAUDE.md + skills/）；這是 Karpathy 對本 workspace 架構的直接理論背書</li><li>Agent-native economy 的 sensors/actuators/logic 分解框架對 SRE 視角高度實用：可直接對應到 monitoring/automation/business-logic 分層</li></ul><hr><h2 id="評分" tabindex="-1">評分 <a class="header-anchor" href="#評分" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;評分&quot;">​</a></h2><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>維度</th><th>分數</th><th>說明</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>A. Workspace 可行動性 (30%)</td><td>9/10</td><td>.md skills 概念直接驗證 cc-workspace 架構；sensors/actuators/logic 分解可作為 agent 設計 rule</td></tr><tr><td>B. 創新性 (20%)</td><td>9/10</td><td>Jaggedness 的 economics 解釋超越 verifiability 框架，是新增洞見</td></tr><tr><td>C. 證據品質 (20%)</td><td>7/10</td><td>menugen/knowledge base 是具體案例，但 jaggedness 解釋仍是理論推導</td></tr><tr><td>D. 技術深度 (15%)</td><td>8/10</td><td>RL 訓練資料分佈、Software 1.0/2.0/3.0 分層有足夠深度</td></tr><tr><td>E. 泛化性 (15%)</td><td>9/10</td><td>框架適用於所有 LLM 應用開發者，非高度特化</td></tr><tr><td><strong>加權總分</strong></td><td><strong>8.5/10</strong></td><td>9×0.3+9×0.2+7×0.2+8×0.15+9×0.15</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>整合決策</strong>：Rule <strong>理由</strong>：Jaggedness economics 解釋 + sensors/actuators/logic 分解框架 → 更新 <code>.claude/rules/harness-design.md</code> 或 <code>karpathy-principles.md</code></p>',23)])])}const p=t(o,[["render",n]]);export{u as __pageData,p as default};
